  <title translate="true">Tip #63</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Heading3"><text styleclass="Heading3" translate="true">Tip of the Day</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:58px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="TipOfTheDayBulb.jpg" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:328px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The entire behaviour of a class, including inherited behaviour, can be displayed in a </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Class</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">System Browser</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> by using the </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Method/Show Inherited Methods</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:normal;" translate="true">menu</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> command.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Since the number of methods in class </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">Object</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is rather large, you can choose to filter these out when displaying all inherited methods. Do this using the </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Method/Filter Object Methods</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> command.</text><snippet src="Tip_Of_The_Day_Footer"/></para>
  </body>
